PLA_CMN_20080714.0245	0	200.0	300.0	speaker	unknown	unknown	Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, July 14 (Reporters Zhao Xiaohui, Tao Junjie) - The China Securities Regulatory Commission announced that the "Pilot Provisions of Compliance Management of Securities Companies" on the 14th, are requiring securities companies to establish directors of compliance by the end of this year and conduct standardized management of securities companies from internal systems.	0	0	0		
PLA_CMN_20080714.0245	0	500.0	600.0	speaker	unknown	unknown	The provisions require securities companies to protect independence, the right to know, and the rights to investigate compliance directors; provide necessary material, financial, and technical support for compliance directors to carry out their jobs, establish or appoint compliance departments, and equip adequate compliance management staff.	0	0	0		
PLA_CMN_20080714.0245	0	600.0	700.0	speaker	unknown	unknown	The provision also requires that securities companies establish reporting systems for irregularities. When departments, branch offices, and its employees discover illegal acts or potential risks in compliance, they should report to the compliance director proactively and timely. For compliance directors and compliance management staff who do quality jobs, their remuneration package should be no less favorable than the average management staff of the same level.	0	0	0		
